record_data.record_plain_text:
Pinnacle Power, LLC
Market Based Rates Tariff
Availability:
Pinnacle Power, LLC makes electric energy and capacity available under this Rate Schedule to any purchaser for resale in the PJM Markets.
Applicability:
This Rate Schedule is applicable to all sales of energy or capacity by Pinnacle Power, LLC not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule of Pinnacle Power, LLC.
Rates:
All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Pinnacle Power, LLC.
Other Terms and Conditions:
All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Pinnacle Power, LLC.
Limitations, Exemptions or Waivers:
Pinnacle Power, LLC has (1) waiver of the filing requirements of Subparts B and C of Part 35, except sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16; (2) waiver of Part 41, regarding accounts, records, and memoranda; Part 101, regarding the uniform system of accounts; and Part 141, with the exception of Part 141.14 and Part 141.15 regarding statements and reports; and blanket authorizations under Part 34 of the Commission's regulations for all future issuances of securities and assumptions of liability. Pinnacle Power, LLC, Docket No. ER14-1792-000
Seller Category:
Seller is a Category 1 Seller in the Northeast Region as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a).
Compliance with Commission Regulations:
Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
Effective Date:
This Tariff shall be effective on the date specified by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
